      • frames

        public static int frames(long millis)
        Returns the number of frames that the specified time takes. This is dependent on the game's frame rate. High frame rate games will take more frames over a specified period of time.
        Parameters:
        millis - time
        Returns:
        number of frames

      • load

        public static final Game load(java.util.Properties props)
                       throws java.io.IOException,
                              java.net.URISyntaxException,
                              java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Create a game using properties defined in the properties file. Changing these properties allows for dynamic construction of games. It also decouples the execution code from the props. This way the game can be played on any number of valid PacMan game boards.
        Parameters:
        props -
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.net.URISyntaxException
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
